  "text": "Leukocyte accumulation is a key component of experimental diabetic retinopathy (DR). [CITATION_1] To enumerate the firmly adhering leukocytes, histological flatmounts from the retinas of normal and diabetic animals were prepared [ Figure 1a ]. Retinal arteries and veins of diabetic animals showed more pronounced leukocyte accumulation compared to those of normal controls [ Figure 1b] .",
